\v 4 Then on that dayВҰ362287 \add вүҲinВҰ362287 late April\add*, I was \add standing\add* on the bank of the greatВҰ362297 riverВҰ362296, i.e., the TigrisВҰ362299.
\v 5 \add вүҲWhenВҰ362301\add* IВҰ362305 looked \add вүҲup, to my surprise\add* there was a manВҰ362307 \add there\add* dressed inВҰ362314 linenВҰ362311 withВҰ362314 a belt of pure goldВҰ362314 from UfazВҰ362315 around his waistВҰ362312.\x + \xo 10:5-6: \xt Rev 1:13-15; 2:18; 19:12.\x*
\v 6 His bodyВҰ362317 \add sparkled\add* like \add вүҲa jewel\add*, his faceВҰ362319 was \add brilliant\add* like lightningВҰ362321, his eyesВҰ362322 were like flaming torchesВҰ362323, his arms and his feetВҰ362326 were like the gleamВҰ362327 of polished bronzeВҰ362328, and his \add вүҲvoice\add* was \add loud\add* like the sound of a \add вүҲhuge crowdВҰ362333\add*.
\p
\v 7 I, Daniel, aloneВҰ362338 saw the vision, because the menВҰ362342 withВҰ362357 me didn'tВҰ362346 see \add вүҲanything\add*. However, \add вүҲthey started tremblingВҰ362352\add* andВҰ362335 ran away to hide,
\v 8 \add вүҲso\add* I was left aloneВҰ362361 and sawВҰ362362 this incredible visionВҰ362365. \add вүҲMy strength deserted\add* me \add and\add* my \add вүҲface went\add* deathlyВҰ362376 pale, and I \add вүҲcouldn't move\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ362381 I heard \add the man\add* \add вүҲstart speaking, andВҰ362381 as he did\add* I fell \add to my knees\add* \add вүҲthenВҰ362381 laid\add* with my face to the groundВҰ362398 in a deep sleep.
\v 10 ThenВҰ362400 \add вүҲsuddenly\add*, a handВҰ362402 touchedВҰ362403 me and set me tremblingВҰ362405 \add back\add* onВҰ362404 my \add вүҲhandsВҰ362410 and\add* kneesВҰ362408.
