\v 11 \add @The man\add* spokeВҰ362432 to me, вҖңDaniel, \add вүҲyou're a man who's greatly valued\add*. I'veВҰ362430 been sent to you, so standВҰ362424 up andВҰ362412 \add вүҲlisten to what\add* I'm aboutВҰ362422 to tell you.вҖқ WhenВҰ362412 he \add вүҲsaid thatВҰ362420\add*, I stoodВҰ362438 up tremblingВҰ362439
\v 12 andВҰ362441 he told me, вҖңDon't be afraid, Daniel, because your \add вүҲprayer\add* was heardВҰ362462 from the \add very\add* firstВҰ362452 dayВҰ362451 thatВҰ362453 you \add вүҲstarted investigating\add* \add these matters\add*. You humbledВҰ362459 yourselfВҰ362459 before your godВҰ362461, \add вүҲso\add* I'veВҰ362466 comeВҰ362466 \add вүҲinВҰ362467 response to\add* your words.
\v 13 ButВҰ362469 the \add вүҲprotector\add* of the Persian kingdomВҰ362471 \add вүҲheld me back for\add* twenty-one days. ThenВҰ362469 wow, Mika'el \add (MichaelВҰ362479)\add*, one of \add &God's\add* chiefВҰ362482 \add вүҲprotectors\add*, cameВҰ362483 to helpВҰ362484 me, because I'd been \add вүҲstuck\add* thereВҰ362487 with the kingsВҰ362489 of PersiaВҰ362472.\x + \xo 10:13,21: \xt Rev 12:7.\x*
\v 14 вҖңNow I'veВҰ362492 come to make you understandВҰ362493 what will happenВҰ362497 to your peopleВҰ362498 in the days \add вүҲnear the end\add*, because this visionВҰ362504 is for \add вүҲthe future\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 While he was \add вүҲtelling me all that\add*, I \add вүҲfaced\add* the ground andВҰ362507 wasn't able to speakВҰ362507.
\v 16 ThenВҰ362516 suddenly, \add вүҲsomeone who resembled a humanВҰ362519\add* touchedВҰ362520 my lipsВҰ362523 and I openedВҰ362524 my mouthВҰ362526 and \add вүҲwas able to speak\add*. I saidВҰ362528 to \add вүҲthe one standingВҰ362531 inВҰ362534 front of\add* me: вҖңMy masterВҰ362533, \add вүҲthat visionВҰ362534 gave me an anxiety attack and I feel weak\add*.
\v 17 How can a servantВҰ362544 of my master \add вүҲlike me be able to talk to someone like you\add*, my master? As for me, \add вүҲI've got no energy left, andВҰ362542 I can barely breatheВҰ362560\add*.вҖқ
\p
